title: McLendon leads Anne Arundel over ACM, 11-2
text:
McLendon leads Anne Arundel over ACM, 11-2 from staff reports The Cumberland Times-News Posted on Sep 30, 2015 by Mike Mathews 
ARNOLD — Garrett McLendon had a first-half hat trick and finished with four goals to lead Anne Arundel Community College to an 11-2 win over Allegany College in a Maryland JUCO men’s soccer match on Tuesday. 
Robert Masters also had four goals and Brandon Long added three for the Pioneers (9-1-1, 6-1 JUCO), who led 6-2 at halftime. 
Matt Simpson and Jerry Washington scored goals for Allegany (1-6, 0-6). Nathan Bodes assisted on Simpson’s goal.
